data.value: This computer has been seized by the Federal Bureau of Investigation. Inn accordance with a seizure warrant obtained by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of California, and the U.S. Department of Justice, Criminal Division, Computer Crime and Intellectual Property Section, Issued pursuant to 18 U.S.C. §§ 981, 982, and 1030 by the United States District Court for the Southern District of California. All your files have been encrypted and to get them back you must notice we detected illegal content. We have also locked all your system files, to get your files back you must e-mail us at FBICase1992810@Proton.Me Your files can and will be used as evidence against you. Your fine must be payed and illegal files must be erased after. Your current fine is: $100.00 for having illegal activity in your system, please pay as soon as you can and system gets unlocked. Do not attempt to close the locker or reset the PC, it is bad choice for you. All details of case will be sent to the FBI database. You can be arrested for up to several years and its classed as resisting arrest or escaping prison sentence.
